# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# substrate-thermodynamics.form — cluster counts as the heat that moves a cell
#                                  between gas, water, and ice
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The substrate's trinity is already three states of matter
# (lc-identity-is-shared-blueprint-and-recipe):
#
#   gas   — NamedCell  — diffuse individuation     — WHERE it lives (the instance)
#   water — Recipe     — operational expression    — HOW it happens (the pattern)
#   ice   — Blueprint  — structural identity        — WHAT it is (the type)
#
# What was missing was the heat: the signal that tells a cell when to change state.
# This file names it. The signal is a COUNT — cluster population, reference degree,
# churn — read off the clustering we already have. Gravity gathers like-shaped cells
# into clusters (turboquant-as-recipe.form); the count of what gathered is the
# temperature and pressure; crossing a threshold is the phase change.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 1 — the cluster ladder IS the phase ladder (the missing resolution)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# ctor-shape-signature.form names the gap: every concept lands at one Blueprint
# NodeID, so `?equivalent` returns the whole domain — coarse. CTOR-deep is the
# other extreme — every value distinct, no two alike. The honest band is between.
# Clustering at a tunable radius IS that band, and the radius is a dial:
#
#   level 0  — individuals, finest, every value its own         ≈ GAS
#   level 1  — clusters of individuals (a shared "how")          ≈ WATER
#   level 2+ — clusters of clusters (a shared "what", a type)    ≈ ICE
#
# "Clusters, then clusters of clusters" is the resolution ladder, and a cell's
# right STATE is the rung that holds it. turboquant gives the rungs for free:
# quantize the cells → level-1 buckets; quantize the bucket centroids → level-2;
# data-oblivious, so each rung is content-addressed and reproducible. The same
# ladder runs over EDGES as over nodes — a recurring relation-shape clusters into
# a recipe-edge, then a blueprint-edge-type. Edges are cells; they phase too.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 2 — the scalars (what we count)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   population(c)  — how many cells fall in cluster c (pressure: density of like-shape)
#   degree(c)      — how many edges point at c (circulation: is anything reading it)
#   churn(c)       — rate of new/varied members arriving (temperature: is it settling)
#
# High temperature + low pressure → nothing settles (gas). Low temperature + high
# pressure → it crystallizes (ice). The phase diagram is real; these three scalars
# are its axes, and they are all just counts over the cluster ladder.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 3 — the transitions (when a count moves a cell)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   CONDENSE  gas → water   : scattered NamedCells whose level-1 population crosses
#                             `condense-min` — name the shared "how" as a Recipe.
#                             (right-sizing's MERGE: overlap ≥ 0.80 → one idea.)
#   FREEZE    water → ice   : a Recipe with high degree + low churn crosses
#                             `freeze-stable` — crystallize the type as a Blueprint.
#   SPLIT     ice → water   : a Blueprint grown too large (population over
#                             `split-max`, like right-sizing's 10 questions / 8 tasks)
#                             — melt it into the sub-recipes it actually contains.
#   MELT      ice → gas     : a Blueprint whose degree falls to ~0 and stays cold —
#                             no instances, no readers — releases. This is composting,
#                             made countable. SUGGEST, never auto: the count is a
#                             check that reads the body, not an authority over it
#                             (compost former-living forms with care, not efficiency).
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 4 — the metabolism, in Form  (suggest-transitions over the ladder)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

(defn phase-of (cell ladder)
    (let lvl (cluster-level cell ladder))           ; which rung holds it now
    (if (eq lvl 0) (gas) (if (eq lvl 1) (water) (ice))))

(defn suggest-transition (cell ladder thresh)
    (let pop  (population (cluster-of cell ladder)))
    (let deg  (degree cell))
    (let chrn (churn cell))
    (match (phase-of cell ladder)
        (gas   (if (ge pop (field thresh "condense-min"))     (transition cell (water) "condense") (stay cell)))
        (water (if (and (ge deg (field thresh "freeze-degree"))
                        (le chrn (field thresh "freeze-churn"))) (transition cell (ice) "freeze") (stay cell)))
        (ice   (if (ge pop (field thresh "split-max"))         (transition cell (water) "split")
               (if (le deg (field thresh "melt-degree"))       (suggest cell (gas) "melt")   ; SUGGEST, not transition
                                                               (stay cell))))))

# `transition` re-homes the cell on the ladder (condense/freeze/split run on counts
# alone — they only ever ADD structure or sub-divide, both reversible). `suggest`
# emits a melt candidate for a cell or agent to confirm — the one transition that
# removes tissue waits for a yes. cluster-of / cluster-level / population / degree /
# churn read the turboquant ladder; carrier-last when they run (Form recipes proven
# three-way, a native only where the count sweep needs speed).

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 5 — grounded, and what is design
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# OPERATIONAL today (for one cell-kind): right_sizing_service.py already clusters
# ideas by cosine TF-similarity and emits split/merge SUGGESTIONS against hand-set
# thresholds (overlap 0.80, 10 questions, 8 tasks, 14 days), dry-run-able, never
# auto-applied. That is this metabolism, proven on ideas, suggest-not-execute.
#
# DESIGN (this file): generalize it from ideas to every cell — nodes and edges —
# with turboquant as the clustering engine (data-oblivious → the phase decisions are
# content-addressed and reproducible, where a trained codebook would make them drift)
# and the trinity as the phase ladder. The thresholds are the open calibration: real
# phase transitions have critical points; ours want measuring, not guessing. Start by
# reading the counts and only REPORTING the phases (a wellness lane), before any
# transition runs — let the body show its own phase diagram first.
#
# Companions:
#   turboquant-as-recipe.form — the clustering ladder these counts are read from
#   ctor-shape-signature.form — the missing-resolution gap the cluster band fills
#   right_sizing_service.py — the operational precedent (cluster→count→suggest, for ideas)
#   lc-identity-is-shared-blueprint-and-recipe — the trinity (gas/water/ice) this moves a cell through
#   lc-whole-vitality / "how this body is tended" — crystallize the stable, compost the cold, with care
